                            Writing Challenges List
                        </div>
                    

                    

                    



                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: right;"><div class="page-rate-widget-box"><span class="rate-points">rating:&nbsp;<span class="number prw54353">+56</span></span><span class="rateup btn btn-default"><a title="I like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, 1)">+</a></span><span class="ratedown btn btn-default"><a title="I don't like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, -1)">&#8211;</a></span><span class="cancel btn btn-default"><a title="Cancel my vote" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.cancelVote(event)">x</a></span></div></div>
<p>Looking for inspiration for your next piece? Want to put your writing skills to the test? Bored and up for some writing shenanigans? Join others and take on a challenge!</p>
<p>This is a list of writing challenges/prompts generated by site members in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-89000">Ideas Critique forum</a>. The list was formerly contained in a <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1043838/challenge-threads">forum thread</a>, but has been moved here for visibility and tidiness.</p>
<p><strong>For a challenge thread to be added here, it must have <span style="text-decoration: underline;">either one or both of</span> the following:</strong><br />
- At least five “I’m interested” or “I’m doing this” comments/posts, from different users. A challenge should be inspirational to authors and encourage discussion!<br />
- At least one successful page on the site that resulted from the challenge. A challenge should produce good work and fun!</p>
<p>Please read the entirety of the challenge thread if you would like to participate in a challenge as an author! The descriptions listed are just small snippets of greater wholes. Happy writing!</p>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2011&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2011&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>9 August 2011 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-381751">Bright’s Challenges</a>: Write an SCP in under 24 hours with no outside help, Roll 2 d23. Go to the cliche list, and make an SCP using the results, and more.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2012&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2012&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>4 April 2012 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-458929">Mann’s Bellerverse Challenge</a>: Come up with a story of the Bellerverse. The setting is effectively sword-and-sorcery, with SCPs standing in for the sorcery.</p>
<p>28 June 2012 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-513784">Roget’s Challenges</a>: These challenges are also designed to help you become a better member of the foundation, whether you are here to critique, write, or be an editor. With HARDMODE.</p>
<p>11 November 2012 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-585458/gears-challange">Gears Challange</a>: So, we're going to peel back the clock a bit, and see how the new kids would have faired.</p>
<p>13 November 2012 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-586457">Djoric’s Challenges</a>: Pre Mass-Edit List, GOIs, and arm-reach item.</p>
<p>16 November 2012 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-589768">Drewbear's Challenges</a>: Involve physical senses, civilian survivors of SCPs, and Google searching your favorite color. on Page 2: tales about a holiday of a GOI, tales about Anomalous Items ended the world and Keters saving it, ultra-short articles, funny tales, make your own pics/audio/etc.</p>
<p>7 December 2012 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-600206">Eric_H Challenges You</a>: The next time you see an SCP that is getting deleted, claim that idea, rewrite it, and make it good enough to stay around.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2013&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2013&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>31 January 2013 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-620784">Wilt's SCP Challenge</a>: Roll dice, and use the tag guide.</p>
<p>18 February 2013 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-625820">Smapti’s Reimagination Theatre</a>: take infamously bad SCPs of yore and write tales that take the core concept and present it in a new light.</p>
<p>4 May 2013 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-649802">SoullessSingularity's Challenges</a>: Roll 2&#160;1d15 for object and effect association, or write a tale that evokes a completely different response from the reader than the SCP object it was based on.</p>
<p>7 May 2013 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-650566">Azzleflux's Challenges</a>: A few different prompts, plus an emotional pit to reference.</p>
<p>12 June 2013 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-661290">Voct’s Challenge</a>: Take the basic ideas of two deleted SCPs, and combine them into something new and — ideally — wonderful.</p>
<p>17 September 2013 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-696993">Bright’s A New Challenge Appears</a>: Write a tale about one or more author avatars! Funny, serious, just plain odd, any sort of tale whatsoever.</p>
<p>5 October 2013 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-704995">Dmatix' Five Word Extravaganza</a>: The challenge is simple: pick five words completely at random (using a random generator) and use all five words as major components in your SCP, and only those five. Also easy mode.</p>
<p>7 November 2013 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-721436">Drewbear's New Challenge</a>: The Home Game: Write a SCP that doesn't have a backstory or narrative attached. It's just something that's weird and mysterious and breaks the laws of reality.</p>
<p>27 December 2013 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-754855">Voct's Challenge 2</a>: Take two random pre-existing SCPs… and devise a connection between them. A tale, a crosstest, a backstory, whatever. Be creative.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2014&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2014&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>19 January 2014 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-764876">Gaffney's Challenge Thread</a>: Historical or religious SCPs? Winners will receive a banana sticker.</p>
<p>6 Feb 2014 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-773041">Scantron's Official Only-Back-For-This-One-Post Challenge Extravaganza</a>: Eight challenges, with easy mode, cookies and brownies for completers.</p>
<p>7 April 2014 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-841576/random-character-generator-challenge">Djoric’s Random Character Generator Challenge</a>: Roll d100 for character faction, sex, age, and personality. Includes Easy, Hard, and Nightmare modes.</p>
<p>4 September 2014 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1014402">Bright’s OFF THE WALL CHALLENGE</a>: post with your never thought it could be done SCP idea, sit back, wait a while, claim someone else’s, and try to make it work.</p>
<p>11 October 2014 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1038502">Ihpkmn's Challenge Thread</a>: Make an Author Avatar, Write an SCP or Tale that’s entirely unplanned, and The Crosslink Challenge!</p>
<p>29 October 2014 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1046254">Fun Time with Dr. Bright!</a>: This is the &quot;Random Groups of People to Make An SCP' CHALLENGE! In which three different randomly-grouped people write containment procedures, description, and then addenda, in that order, building off the previous sections. Read more to join the groups.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2015&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2015&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>2 January 2015 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1073383/">Hysteria's Challenge</a>: Aka, give the person above you a picture.</p>
<p>27 January 2015 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1089474/">DreamwalkerFae's TvTropes Challenge</a>: Write an SCP based off of one of two random tropes generated by the TvTropes site. Hard mode: Use both tropes.</p>
<p>10 February 2015 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1107457">Decibelle's Challenges</a>: A series of five challenges involving things you don't like, short containment procedures for non-Safe class SCPs, and random number generators.</p>
<p>5 March 2015 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1140769/">Randomini's Flash Tale Challenge</a>: Three characters you didn't write, 1000 words or less, no peer review. Includes optional and impossible mode.</p>
<p>13 March 2015 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1147092/">Zyn's Kawaii Insect Melodies</a>: Pick a cute bug or two, pick lyrics from a SID song or two. Hard mode: write a love story.</p>
<p>7 July 2015 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1271813">&quot;Tag-Free&quot; SCP Challenge</a>: Go and look at the Tag Guide, and then try and write something that doesn't fall into any previously defined categories.</p>
<p>25 September 2015 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1378332/">MrWrong's Fill Up the SCP Map Challenge</a>: Your challenge, should you choose to accept, is to make an SCP found/manifested in a country/dependency/state/province/sub-national division that has no SCPs.</p>
<p>5 December 2015 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1468460/">DEXANOTE'S CHALLENGE</a>: The challenge is this: A Tale about two SCPs in conflict. Dull, right? I thought so too. But the catch is, you must write it from the perspective of a civilian.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2016&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2016&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>8 May 2016 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1703757">LordStonefish's Pick N' Mix Challenge</a>: Pick three terms from the list provided and create a concept out of them. Then write it up. Make them as strange and random as you want.</p>
<p>29 August 2016 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1815424">SCP Ideas That Would Never Ever Work</a>: An open forum prompt generator thread! I'd like to hear your ideas… or rather your TERRIBLE ideas. Be sure to at least make them plausible in some context.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2017&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2017&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>10 February 2017 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-2116184">Log of Anomalous Tales</a>: Pick an item from the log-of-anomalous-items, and make an interesting tale about it.</p>
<p>10 August 2017 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-3244956">Randomized Horror Story Challenge</a>: Using a horror story plot generator, write a scary SCP article.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2018&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2018&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>9 January 2018 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-4819645">Underloved Series I</a>: Choose a Series I skip without any tales (under <a href="/scp-series-1-tales-edition">this list</a>) and write a tale about it.</p>
<p>2 April 2018 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-5666847">Become What You Hate</a>: Go to the <a href="http://scpper.com/search">scpper database</a>, find the list of tags pertaining to articles you've upvoted. Take the three lowest and write an SCP with those.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2019&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2019&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>2 January 2019 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-9813270/writing-challenge:tag-golf">Tag Golf</a>: Come up with a combination of two attribute tags that haven't been used together before, then write something that uses them.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2020&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2020&nbsp;Challenges</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>22 April 2020 - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-13262147/writing-challenge-impostor-syndrome">Imposter Syndrome</a>: Write an SCP in the style, tone, formatting, and subject matter of a different author, without getting critique or advice from said author.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<p>Note: If you’ve made a new challenge thread and it could use more attention, you may make a post in this page discussion proclaiming the glory and awesomeness of your new challenge thread. One post per challenge thread; duplicates or bump posts will be deleted. Keep it fair to all new challenge-makers!</p>

